    вҖ–T (f + g) xвҖ–вӮ‘ вүӨ вҖ–T f x + T g xвҖ–вӮ‘)
  (T_submul : вҲҖ (a : рқ•Ӯ) (f : Оұ вҶ’ рқ•Ӯ) (x : Оұ'), вҖ–T (a вҖў f) xвҖ–вӮ‘ вүӨ вҖ–aвҖ–вӮ‘ вҖў вҖ–T f xвҖ–вӮ‘)
  (weakly_cont_T : вҲҖ {f : Оұ вҶ’ рқ•Ӯ} {fs : в„• вҶ’ Оұ вҶ’ рқ•Ӯ}
                     (f_locInt : LocallyIntegrable f Ој)
                     (hF_meas : вҲҖ (n : в„•), AEStronglyMeasurable (fs n) Ој)
                     (h_norm_monotone : вҲҖ (a : Оұ), Monotone (fun n вҶҰ вҖ–fs n aвҖ–))
                     (h_lim : вҲҖ (a : Оұ), Filter.Tendsto (fun (n : в„•) => fs n a) Filter.atTop (nhds (f a)))
                     (G : Set Оұ'),
    eLpNorm (T f) 1 (ОҪ.restrict G) вүӨ Filter.limsup (fun n вҶҰ eLpNorm (T (fs n)) 1 (ОҪ.restrict G)) Filter.atTop)

    :

  --(weakly_cont_T : WeaklyContinuous T Ој ОҪ) : --TODO: correct assumption with modified T
    --TODO: might have to adjust the constant
    HasLorentzType T p 1 p вҲһ Ој ОҪ (4 * c / p) := by
  intro f hf
  --have hp : 1 вүӨ p := by sorry --use: should follow from hpp'
  have claim : вҲҖ (G : Set Оұ'), (MeasurableSet G) вҶ’ (ОҪ G < вҲһ) вҶ’ eLpNorm (T f) 1 (ОҪ.restrict G)
    вүӨ (4 * c / p) * eLorentzNorm f p 1 Ој * (ОҪ G) ^ p'вҒ»В№.toReal := by
      intro G measurable_G G_finite
      rcases hf with вҹЁaemeasurable_f, hfвҹ©
      revert f --TODO: go on here
      apply AEStronglyMeasurable.induction
      В· intro f g stronglyMeasurable_f hfg hf hg
        have : eLorentzNorm f p 1 Ој < вҠӨ := by
          sorry --use: hg
        have hf := hf this
        sorry --use: hf
      intro g stronglyMeasurable_g hg
```

This is the main lemma. It's trying to prove that `T` has the Lorentz type property. The proof strategy is to use induction on `g` which is `Оұ вҶ’ K`.

Now, we need to prove the base case and inductive steps. Let's continue with the structure:

```tactics
      set gвӮҒ := fun x вҶҰ Real.toNNReal (RCLike.re (g x))
      set gвӮӮ := fun x вҶҰ Real.toNNReal (- RCLike.re (g x))
      set gвӮғ := fun x вҶҰ Real.toNNReal (RCLike.im (g x))
      set gвӮ„ := fun x вҶҰ Real.toNNReal (- RCLike.im (g x))
      have g_decomposition : g = (1 : рқ•Ӯ) вҖў (algebraMap в„қ рқ•Ӯ вҲҳ NNReal.toReal вҲҳ gвӮҒ)
                                + (-1 : рқ•Ӯ) вҖў (algebraMap в„қ рқ•Ӯ вҲҳ NNReal.toReal вҲҳ gвӮӮ)
                                + (RCLike.I : рқ•Ӯ) вҖў (algebraMap в„қ рқ•Ӯ вҲҳ NNReal.toReal вҲҳ gвӮғ)
                                + (-RCLike.I : рқ•Ӯ) вҖў (algebraMap в„қ рқ•Ӯ вҲҳ NNReal.toReal вҲҳ gвӮ„) := by
        unfold gвӮҒ gвӮӮ gвӮғ gвӮ„
        ext x
        simp only [one_smul, neg_smul, Pi.add_apply, Function.comp_apply, Real.coe_toNNReal',
          Pi.neg_apply, Pi.smul_apply, smul_eq_mul]
        ring_nf
        rw [algebraMap]
        sorry --TODO: simple algebra
```

This decomposes `g` into four real-valued functions `gвӮҒ, gвӮӮ, gвӮғ, gвӮ„` such that `g` can be written as a linear combination of these functions with coefficients in `в„Ӯ`.

Now, the proof continues with defining `T'` and proving its properties:

