import Mathlib
open Filter Real Measure Set

/-!
The theorem states that for a linear map T between two normed spaces, the Lorentz norm of T is bounded by a multiple of the product of the Lorentz norm of the input function and the volume of the target set, raised to the power of the conjugate exponent.
Specifically, if T is a linear map from Оұ to Оұ' with measures Ој and ОҪ, and c is a positive constant, then for a function f : Оұ вҶ’ K (where K is a RCLike field), if f is p-Lorentz integrable, then:
вҖ–T fвҖ–_{L^p(ОҪ)} вүӨ c / p * вҖ–fвҖ–_{L^p(Ој)} * ОҪ(G)^{p'}
where p' is the Holder conjugate of p, and G is a measurable set of finite measure.
The proof proceeds by decomposing the function f into its real and imaginary parts, and then applying properties of Lorentz norms and linear maps.
-/

theorem RCLike.norm_I {K : Type u_1} [RCLike K] : вҖ–(RCLike.I : K)вҖ– = if RCLike.I вү  (0 : K) then 1 else 0 := by
  split_ifs with h
  В· apply RCLike.norm_I_of_ne_zero h
  В· push_neg at h
    simpa

lemma HasRestrictedWeakType.hasLorentzType [TopologicalSpace Оұ] {рқ•Ӯ : Type*} /- [MeasurableSpace Оө'] [BorelSpace Оө'] -/
  --[ENormedAddMonoid Оө']
